        "label": "What's Going On With the Leafs",
        "body": "The Leafs' playoff pulse flatlined another night in Dallas&mdash;<strong>a gut-wrenching 5-6 overtime loss</strong> on Apr. 13 that capped their home finale with fireworks but no finish, blowing two leads in a season that's slipped into the abyss at 32-35-14, eighth in the Atlantic, 35 games back with 78 points and an L6 streak carving deeper scars. John Tavares rallied with a goal and assist in the chaos, but the core&mdash;Mitch Marner long gone, Auston Matthews and William Nylander shouldering a fading dream&mdash;couldn't stem the bleed from defensive lapses and goaltending woes that have torpedoed this Original Six hope machine. What went right? Bursts of offense, sure, 5 goals against a 32&ndash;35&ndash;14-12 Stars juggernaut. What cratered? Everything else, as this 15th-seed wild-card lock claws for dignity heading into Ottawa. Tonight's the hour&mdash;<strong>6:30 PM ET at the Senators</strong>, where a spark could salvage pride or seal the tomb before Hurricanes hell awaits.",
        "updated": "Updated April 15, 2026"
      },
