      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Jays",
        "body": "Vladimir Guerrero Jr. ripped a go-ahead double in the 10th&mdash;clutch as ever&mdash;to snatch a wild <strong>7&ndash;9 win over the Brewers</strong> last night, snapping Toronto's skid and igniting faint hope in a road trip that desperately needed it. At 7-9, the Blue Jays cling to fourth in the AL East, three games back with a playoff seed of 11 and that fragile one-game streak; they've clawed from two straight losses to Minnesota, but the early-season stumbles&mdash;echoing the Yankees' fade&mdash;demand urgency. Vlad's heroics masked a bullpen wobble in extra innings, yet no fresh injuries cloud the clubhouse, leaving the lineup's fire to carry them. This isn't contender champagne yet&mdash;Rays le7&ndash;9t 10-6&mdash;but it's a pulse. <strong>Tonight's rubber match at Milwaukee, 6:40 ET, tests if they sweep or stumble back into mediocrity</strong>; win it, and the trajectory flips&mdash;lose, and the hunt grows colder. Jays Nation, breathe.",
        "updated": "Updated April 15, 2026"
      },
