      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Raptors",
        "body": "The Raptors' faithful have waited two long years for this moment&mdash;playoff basketball returns to Scotiabank Arena, where the ghosts of 2019 still whisper championship dreams. On the final gasp of the regular season, <strong>Toronto clinched the No. 5 seed in the East with a gritty win, dodging a Knicks showdown for this blood feud against the Cavaliers</strong>, their Atlantic Division rivals now standing between them and deeper glory. At 46-36, third in the division but riding a W1 streak into the fray, the Raptors enter as hungry underdogs&mdash;5 games back in the playoff pecking order, yet pulsing with that Nurse-era fire. Scottie Barnes is the beating heart here, his two-way menace the X-factor that could shred Cleveland's stars if the bench doesn't implode; whispers from camp say he's locked in, no nagging tweaks. The defense that carried them through the slog must feast early&mdash;expect Donovan Mitchell to test it ruthlessly. Game 1 tips tomorrow night in Cleveland, a cauldron where Toronto's road warriors can steal momentum or shatter. <strong>Watch Barnes own the paint; one explosive opener could flip this series on its head</strong>.",
        "updated": "Updated April 15, 2026"
      },
